         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden 11/6/69. ¶  ¶ I cannot forego the pleasure, dear Mr Horne, to bid you at least by a few lines my best farewell, and to express to you at the eve of your departure from these shor...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.06.11a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Richard Horne</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Vol. 5, pp. 227-30, Richard Hengist Horne papers, MLMSS 2410, Mitchell Library, State Library of NSW, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden 11/6/69.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I cannot forego the pleasure, dear Mr Horne, to bid you at least by a few lines my best farewell, and to express to you at the eve of your departure from these shores my admiration for your talents and writings, my appreciation of all your highly honorable sentiments and my sympathy<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for your future. It was my wish to have shaken hands with you once more, but as I am not yet fully recovered from a severe bronchial catarrh, I am compelled to remain within the walls of my dwelling, as far as it is possible. Permit me to offer the enclosed poor photogram for your friendly acceptance, &amp; let me receive yours as a souvenir for the series of little pictures of celebrated friends.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No image of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Horne<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been identified at MEL, but see M to J. Haast, 29 July 1862 (in this edition as 62-07-29b) and notes thereto.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I can be here of any service to you, when you are in Europe, again, pray command my attention.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With the most regardful wishes for your future</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">R. H. Horne Esq</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Passenger by the Lady Jocelyn<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Lady Jocelyn</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sailed from Melbourne for London on 12 June 1869, with Horne registered as a passenger.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The letter is annotated in another hand: ‘if not at address, return to J. K. White &amp; Co. Collins [St] Melbourne’.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Robe Street</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">St Kilda</p>
